25|$|<b>CFA</b> <b>francs</b> {{are used}} in {{fourteen}} countries: twelve formerly French-ruled nations in West and Central Africa, Guinea-Bissau (a former Portuguese colony), and Equatorial Guinea (a former Spanish colony). These fourteen countries have a combined population of 147.5million people (as of 2013), and a combined GDP of US$166.6billion (as of 2012). The ISO currency codes are XAF for the Central African <b>CFA</b> <b>franc</b> and XOF for the West African <b>CFA</b> <b>franc.</b>|$|R
